<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - High-pressure Oil Pump - Removal
        - High-pressure Oil Pump and Drive Gear
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="5">
        <title>High-pressure Oil Pump and Drive Gear</title>
        <figure id="f1201106" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg9/EG9136.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Removing High-pressure Oil Supply Hoses</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure Oil Pump</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Supply Hoses</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Clamp</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the special removal tool to disconnect the high-pressure oil supply hoses at the pump
                and at each cylinder head. Cap the fittings.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the electrical harness from the IPR valve solenoid.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2051101" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg9/EG9139.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Removing Drive Gear Access Cover</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Drive Gear Access Cover</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting Bolt (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two bolts and the drive gear access cover from the front cover. Clean all RTV
                sealant from the access cover and front cover mating surface.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201105" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3283.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Removing Drive Gear Bolt</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Drive Gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting Bolt and Washer</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bolt and washer that secure the drive gear to the high-pressure oil pump.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201108" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3511A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Removing High-pressure Oil Pump Mounting Bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Drive Gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure Oil Pump</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting Bolts</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two capscrews that secure high-pressure oil pump to front cover. Remove pump and
                gasket from front cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The gasket is reusable.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure>
            <graphic filename="../figF13/F1314.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="592px"
                     box="yes"/>
            <caption>Removing Drive Gear</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front Cover</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Drive Gear</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear through the top of the front cover.</para>
        </step1>
